An embleme of the times or, a seasonable exhortation drawn from the consideration of Gods gracious dealing with England, above all other her neighbour-nations.
1 sheet ([1] p.) : ill.
Printed by R.A., London : 1647.
In verse: "Englands admired change, who can ascend?" ... Illustrated with allegorical engraving. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Jan: 19th 1646"; the '7' in the imprint has been crossed out. Reproduction of the originals in the British Library.
